description:
A shabby cane.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Ray of Light
name: Remnant Staff
note:
<dPlnText:An unreliable wand made of branches.
Not used as a catalyst, but for striking.
　
It has lost the blessing of the stars
that once shone so brightly in the past.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A durable wooden stick.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Batting
name: Sturdy Stick
note:
<dPlnText:A polished wooden stick.
A very simple and easy-to-use weapon
with decent batting power.
　
Anything that lives on Mana can be
convinced by hitting them hard enough.
Monsters follow this rule as well.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A tool for splitting firewood.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Fighting Spirit
name: Woodsplitter
note:
<dPlnText:An axe for splitting firewood.
High killing power despite not being a weapon.
　
Though it easily splits flesh and blood,
striking hard shells or metals are not recommended.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A sword imbued with magical power.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Magical Blade
name: Magical Sword
note:
<dPlnText:A weapon imbued with magical power.
It can be sharpened to unleash a magical blade.
　
The sword itself is ordinary
with no special features to speak of.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A weapon that fires bullets with the power of Mana.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Penetrator
name: Mana Shooter
note:
<dPlnText:A handgun popular with locals.
Functions using the user's Mana.
　
Note that the weapon does not fire Mana,
but fires bullets using the power of Mana.
You'll get stares if you get this wrong.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate +5%>

description:
A glowing blue wand.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Explosive Magic
name: Blue Wand
note:
<dPlnText:A high-quality catalyst.
Exhibits a magical glow.
　
The blue glow is a sign of magical power.
Even should the user's ability be inferior,
a certain amount of power is still displayed.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate +5%>

description:
A weapon that is both a staff and a sword.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Magical Blade
name: Ruins Swordstaff
note:
<dPlnText:A unique weapon from Virea.
Has the nature of both sword and staff.
　
Maybe because the Sky Ruins are from
such an ancient age, such items that
are considered rare, even on Ordowald,
have become commonplace in this place.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate +5%>

description:
A special cane created by the Flower Fairies.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Flower Healing, Flower Quake
name: Flower Wand
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A gift from the Dryads.
Filled with much appreciation.
　
The magical power of the colorful
flower begets life and death.
　
Has the following special effects:
・SP Cost -10%>

description:
A deteriorated metal rod.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Batting
name: Rusty Tool
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A metal rod.
It has rusted and deteriorated greatly.
　
It's not a weapon to begin with,
and it's not in good condition either,
but its power is surprisingly decent.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate -100%>

description:
A handmade fishing pole.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Hook
name: Fishing Rod
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A fishing rod made from tree branches and vines.
Considering the materials, it's surprisingly well made.
　
It's a tool with no lethal power.
To bring such a thing into battle
carelessly may incur the enemies' wrath.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Chance to be targeted +1000%>

description:
A mechanical sword with a red-hot blade.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Laser Cutting
name: Electric Sword
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A sword that heats up to a high temperature.
Its properties allow it to cut through metal.
　
The heat is amplified by magical power,
so talent is required to maximize performance.
　
It has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Fire attribute>

description:
A spear wielded by Ant Knights.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Sharp Stabbing
name: Spear of Jamlov
note:
<NameColor:23>
<BoostEX:CR, 30>
<dPlnText:A spear with a needle-like blade.
Used by knights of a castle that once existed.
　
Long ago, a queen ruled over many different 
races and protected the peace of Tantali.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate +20%
・Critical DMG +30%>

description:
A wand that regained its light.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Star Dragon Radiance
name: Star Dragon's Staff
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:The staff Ino held from the beginning.
With the stars' blessing, it regained its radiance.
　
That child had never been abandoned.
As the forerunner of hope he departed
in pursuit of that unleashed "Calamity".
　
However, having regained his human body,
he paid the price with his memories.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Light attribute>

description:
A weapon that remained in someone's memory.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Master Stroke, Effervescent Magic
name: Sword of Tradition
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Equipment woven from memories.
High quality and easy to use.
　
That which excels are memorable,
our enemies also. And that is why
we must respond with that same power.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate +8%>

description:
The horns of a mountain-like beast.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Slamming
name: Large Horn Hammer
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Battle spoils from a powerful enemy.
The giant horn of the Peak of Auli.
　
A sturdy and solid symbol of the king of beasts. 
When wielded, its power can shake the earth.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Recovers 5% HP each Turn>

description:
A needle that shines in complex colors.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Rainbow Encounter
name: Rainbow Needle
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Battle spoils from a powerful enemy.
An object that seems unreal.
　
The soft-bodied monster drifted in the sea
in the distant sky, and witnessed
something that cannot be described.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Non-Wave DMG taken -10%>

description:
A weapon woven from Ino's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Star Dragon Radiance, Wave of Myth
name: Calamity Star Staff
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:The staff Ino had held, transformed.
Darkness nestles in the starlight.
　
Many times, the world ends and begins anew.
And in between each such scene stands
two figures, a boy and a girl.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Light and Dark attributes
・Recovers 10% SP each Turn
・Recovers 10 TP each Turn>

description:
A weapon woven from Ino's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Star Dragon Radiance, Wave of Myth
name: Calamity Star Staff+1
note:
<NameColor:27>
<dPlnText:The staff Ino had held, transformed.
Darkness nestles in the starlight.
　
Many times, the world ends and begins anew.
And in between each such scene stands
two figures, a boy and a girl.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Light and Dark attributes
・Recovers 15% SP each Turn
・Recovers 15 TP each Turn>

description:
A weapon of the knights who forgot death.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Exile's Spear, Mystic Integration
name: Spear of the Exiled Nation
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A spear forged in a crater. 
Wielded by a knight for slaying a dragon.
　
That kingdom that once existed was
born in the flames, lived with the flames,
and in the end perished with the flames.
　
Has the following special effects:
・DEF and MDF +10%>

description:
Weapons wielded by the knights who forgot death.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Exile's Spear, Mystic Integration
name: Spear of the Exiled Nation+1
note:
<NameColor:27>
<dPlnText:A spear forged in a crater. 
Wielded by a knight for slaying a dragon.
　
That kingdom that once existed was
born in the flames, lived with the flames,
and in the end perished with the flames.
　
Has the following special effects:
・DEF and MDF +15%>

description:
Equipment belonging to Adventurer Luora.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Heavy Slash, Twin Swords Dance
name: Sword Demon's Twin Blades
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A pair of swords wielded by Luora.
Seems too heavy to be one-handed.
　
The blade harbors many scars, boasting of
the long time they fought alongside the Lord.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A weapon used by monsters.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Precise Attack
name: Sharp Claws
note:
<dPlnText:A pair of sharpened claws.
Any monster can use it with ease.
　
Other races can also use monster weapons,
but everyone agreed it didn't feel right.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A dagger wielded by Little Barbarians.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Precise Attack
name: Monster Dagger
note:
<dPlnText:A very small dagger.
The sharpness leaves a lot to be desired.
　
Only when it is used by a monster
will its true worth be realized.
　
No special effects.>

description:
An easy-to-hold stone.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Triple Attack
name: Stone Fist
note:
<dPlnText:A lump of stone.
You attack by smacking with it.
　
It may not be a real weapon, but
its power is close enough to one.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A weapon imbued with the prayers of monsters.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Flying Slash
name: Blade of Prayer
note:
<dPlnText:A deadly weapon.
The blade is sharp and imbued with magic.
　
Usually, the prayers of monsters are simple.
For instance, this weapon was simply
prayed for to be strong.
　
No special effects.>

description:
Standard equipment for Machine Dolls.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Precise Attack
name: Machine Doll Sword
note:
<dPlnText:Machine Doll equipment.
It bears a weight no human can wield.
　
As it's something for Machine Dolls,
anyone else holding this weapon is
a violation in the Upper Layer.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A magical weapon used by monsters.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Explosive Magic
name: Magic Branch
note:
<dPlnText:A small wooden branch with magical power.
Any monster can use it with ease.
　
Other races can also use monster weapons,
but everyone agreed it didn't feel right.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A ritual tool passed down among barbarians.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Explosive Magic
name: Rustic Stick
note:
<dPlnText:A tool for a certain ritual.
Used by Barbarians known as Sorcerers.
　
Such Barbarian Sorcerers are no more,
as their cruelty was shunned even by
their own people.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A magical book that can only be read by monsters.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Spread Magic
name: Monster Knowledge
note:
<dPlnText:The first thing a Magician writes down.
It contains the basics of magic.
　
Magicians originally referred only to 
a race of monsters. Their way of life
then became a guide, establishing the title.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A tool that concentrates magical power in the hand.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Magic Bludgeoning
name: Magic Hand
note:
<dPlnText:Gloves that collect magical power.
And then beats the enemy with it.
　
Humans would say it's convenient, but
those that are adept at manipulating magic
would've just done it themselves anyway.
　
No special effects.>

description:
Prototype equipment for Machine Dolls.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Explosive Magic
name: Machine Doll Staff
note:
<dPlnText:Machine Doll equipment.
It bears a weight no human can wield.
　
As it's something for Machine Dolls,
anyone else holding this weapon is
a violation in the Upper Layer.
　
No special effects.>

description:
A book created by a Barbarian Sorcerer.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Fang Sorcery
name: Barbarian Spellbook
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A blood-stained, abominable book.
It is sealed with violent sorcery.
　
In the long past era of Ront's early days,
heretical Barbarians ruled the mountains.
The sorcery created through such horrific
rituals was later buried by their Lord.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate +5%>

description:
The fangs that fell from a snake monster.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]毒穿ち
name: Venomous Fang
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Fangs that still ooze poison.
Any monster can use it as a weapon.
　
Its sharpness is maintained by poison,
always filled with murderous intent.
　
In the past, when a queen ruled the Snake Women,
it was said no infighting existed in the races.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Negate ATK Down
・Negate Great ATK Down>

description:
An old hunter's weapon.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Ice Arrow
name: Snow Hunter's Bow
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A weapon of the one-renowned Snow Hunters.
It chooses its master, and only monsters can wield it.
　
The Snow Hunters braved the cold that 
covered the planet, but no living creature
can truly defeat the threat of nature.
　
However, the will to live for one's comrades 
is still passed down to this day.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Negate Blind>

description:
Tetra Devices' arms.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Beam Module
name: Tetra Bit
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A mechanical weapon of Int'oma.
A special weapon that requires focus to operate.
　
Tetra Devices are protectors of the Sky Ruins.
When they fell down, all that approaches
seemed to them as if they are invaders.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Remove 5 TP every Turn>

description:
A Crab Monster's claws.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Blowing Bubbles
name: Crab Scissors
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Crab claws in good condition.
Fresh and without a single scratch.
　
It feels like a blunt weapon
and also feels like armor.
　
It can also foam at the "mouth".
　
Has the following special effects:
・Negate Stun>

description:
A blunt instrument covered in thorns.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Bone Splitting
name: Emperor's Rebuke
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A sinister blunt weapon.
It will most certainly inflict pain.
　
It seems to have been swung countless times.
The wear is obvious, the thorns covered in blood.
　
Fear is due to not believing.
Those wounds are one caused by love.
　
Has the following special effects:
・TP Gain Rate +50%>

description:
A type of weapon for Machine Dolls.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]None
name: Missile Shooter
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Special weapon of the Machine Dolls.
Shoots out small missiles.
　
There are no rules for Machine Doll weapons.
Each one comes up with and develops their own.
To see such ambitious creations is rare in itself.
　
Has the following special effects:
・AGI +200 when Normal Attacking>

description:
A certain Succubus's self-defense method.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Yotogi's Secret
name: Yotogi's Dagger
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:A Shikinowa-style dagger.
The sheath is characterized by its lustrous decoration.
　
In the nation on the eastern island,
Succubi are known as Yotogi, and enjoys
a different status from other places.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Recovers 4 TP every Turn>

description:
A weapon once used by the Priestess of Stagnation.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Rite of Stagnation
name: Priestess's Cortege
note:
<BoostEX:MG, 10>
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Ordowald's treasure.
Its blade is shaped by magical power.
　
The Priestess once lived at the bottom
of the dark sea, and calmed the pulses
of stasis with the Rite of Stagnation.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Magical Attacks Power +10%>

description:
A weapon that remained in someone's memory.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Master Stroke, Effervescent Magic
name: Legendary Blade
note:
<NameColor:23>
<dPlnText:Equipment woven from memories.
High quality and easy to use.
　
That which excels are memorable,
our enemies also. And that is why
we must respond with that same power.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate +8%>

description:
A weapon of the Machine Dolls.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Burst Shot
name: Beam Rifle
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Battle spoils from a powerful enemy.
Tangled in the roots of a mutated thunder tree.
　
A weapon hardly suited for Kertailt.
Someone probably dropped it by accident
and got it snagged in some roots.
　
Has the following special effects:
・AGI +100 when Normal Attacking>

description:
鞭のようにしなる炎の夜魔の髪。
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]魔力回帰
name: Kannryuua's Hair
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Battle spoils from a powerful enemy.
The source of the Magma Dragonfish's power.
　
It appears to have once held great flames within,
but it has since burned out, and only
magical power remains within.
　
Has the following special effects:
・MAT +5%>

description:
Ritual implements used in Sorcerer rituals.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Flame Hex
name: Barbarian Staff
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Battle spoils from a powerful enemy.
The cursed ritual implement.
　
At some point, rituals became controlled 
by the implement, and the Sorcerers mere 
pawns that followed their every order.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Negate Confusion>

description:
The weapons used by twin robots.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Spiral Inject
name: Drill Unit
note:
<NameColor:31>
<dPlnText:Battle spoils from a powerful enemy.
Weapons given to the Mechanical Twins.
　
An excavation machine once used to
expand the ruins, which was
the Twins' original mission.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical Rate +10%>

description:
A weapon used by Talvirar's hunters.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Concentration, Binding Tool
name: Multi-Binder
note:
<NameColor:2>
<BoostEX:CR, 30>
<dPlnText:The hunters' restraining weapon.
Used by those with superior skill.
　
A hunter's weapons should always be hidden.
Giving such things to someone else
is a sign of absolute trust.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Critical DMG +30%>

description:
A weapon woven from Kannryuua's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Flaming Climax
name: Twisted Uneven Horns
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the power of the 
Lord of Reason, a glimpse of which can be wielded.
　
The horns of the Flame Succubus are irregularly distorted 
because she could not withstand her own magical power, 
and they have become a symbol of her power.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Fire attribute
・Recovers 10 TP every Turn
・Negate Poison>

description:
A weapon woven from Valco's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Thunderstrike
name: Thundercurse Sacrifice
note:
<NameColor:2>
<反撃拡張:雷呪の贄>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the power of the 
Lord of Reason, a glimpse of which can be wielded.
　
The villagers feared the curse of thunder, 
so they offered many sacrifices to the great tree, 
never realizing that itself was a curse.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Thunder attribute
・Counterattacks on receiving Physical DMG
・Negate Forgetful>

description:
A weapon woven from Muracca's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Ice Impact
name: Ice Claws of the Mad Hunt
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the power of the 
Lord of Reason, a glimpse of which can be wielded.
　
A hunter hunts to live, but she
must not hunt to survive in vain.
Therefore, she had fallen to madness.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Ice attribute
・Critical and Evasion Rate +10%
・Negate Confusion>

description:
A weapon woven from Kilma's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Sword of Regression
name: Blade of Resting Stasis
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the power of the 
Lord of Reason, a glimpse of which can be wielded.
　
Sin sinks to the bottom, landing in stasis.
The Rite of Stagnation, the Priest's duty,
in the end was shattered by thoughtlessness.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Water attribute
・Physical and Magical DMG taken -10%
・Negate Fatigue>

description:
A weapon woven from Kilma's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Crystal Polish
name: Slaughter's Greatsword
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the power of the 
Lord of Reason, a glimpse of which can be wielded.
　
Numerous scars remain on the pair of swords.
They are not evidence of the unending fight,
but the unwavering will to protect everyone.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Earth attribute
・ATK +10%
・Negate Paralyze>

description:
A weapon woven from Tyvar's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Storm Embrace
name: Samsara's Vortex
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the power of the 
Lord of Reason, a glimpse of which can be wielded.
　
Dragons from ages past have gathered on 
the Zephyr Continent, waiting for their 
old friends in their sacred shrine.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Wind attribute
・Recover 10% HP every Turn
・Negate Stun>

description:
A weapon woven from Kannryuua's memories.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Flaming Climax
name: Twisted Uneven Horns+1
note:
<NameColor:27>
<dPlnText:A weapon that inherits the power of the 
Lord of Reason, a glimpse of which can be wielded.
　
The horns of the Flame Succubus are irregularly distorted 
because she could not withstand her own magical power, 
and they have become a symbol of her power.
　
Has the following special effects:
・Attacks gain the Fire attribute
・Recovers 15 TP every Turn
・Negate Poison>

description:
A weapon of the knights who forgot death. Distorted.
\C[24]Weapon Skill: \C[0]Exile's Spear, Mystic Integration
name: Distorted Spear of the Exiled Nation
note:
<NameColor:2>
<dPlnText:A spear forged in a crater.
